description: From Middle English *overthenken, *overthenchen (compare Middle English overthinken (“to grieve; have regrets; be sorry; be anxious”)), from Old English oferþenċan (“to think over; consider”), equivalent to over- +‎ think.

verbs.description: overthink (third-person singular simple present overthinks, present participle overthinking, simple past and past participle overthought)
overthink (third-person singular simple present overthinks, present participle overthinking, simple past and past participle overthought)

entries.meaning: To think or analyze too much.
examples: Don't overthink the problem. It's not that difficult.
